obo:HP_0003798 obo:IAO_0000115 Nemaline rods are abnormal bodies that can occur in skeletal muscle fibers. The rods can be observed on histological analysis of muscle biopsy tissue or upon electron microscopy, where they appear either as extensions of sarcomeric Z-lines, in random array without obvious attachment to Z-lines often in areas devoid of sarcomeres or in large clusters localized at the sarcolemma or intermyofibrillar spaces.
